# Only the Go services (tenancy-service, claims-gateway, registry-service,
# provisioner) build with a repo-root context — they need sibling Go modules
# (auth-contracts, auth-middleware) that a per-service context can't reach.
# Everything else still builds with its own directory as context and never
# sees this file. Keep this list tight: it's the difference between a
# multi-GB and a multi-MB build context for those four Dockerfiles.
.git
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/target
**/coverage
client
landing-page
documentation
simulators
k8s
**/*.md
